  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals in certain industries are typically required to report suspicious transactions or activities that may indicate money laundering. Specific requirements can vary by jurisdiction, but generally include:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting to financial intelligence units\n2. Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n3. Maintaining transaction records\n4. Filing Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs)\n5. Potential penalties for failure to report\n\nExact details depend on local laws and regulations.",
